The following table details the number 
of U.S. adults who had serious thoughts of suicide, made a plan, or  
attempted suicide during the previous year by state, according to  
data from the National Survey on Drug Use and Health.   According to the report, in 2008, a total of 35,045 deaths,
197,838 hospitalizations, and 323,342 emergency department visits
were reported. The following data is in thousands, ranked by total.  SOURCE: National Survey on Drug Use and Health  To contact the reporter on this story:
